James MORRISON, Appellant, v. WARDEN OF UNITED STATES PENITENTIARY, ATLANTA, GEORGIA, Appellee. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. October 25, 1929. No. 5593. James Morrison, in pro. per. Clint W. Hager, U. S. Atty., and Hal Lindsay, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Atlanta, Ga., for appellee.

Before WALKER, BRYAN, and FOSTER, Cireuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment in the above numbered and entitled cause is affirmed.
